  "prompt": "How is the placement at IIHMR Jaipur?",
  "response": "IIHMR University Jaipur (Institute of Hotel Management, Catering Technology, and Applied Nutrition, Research and Management) is renowned for its strong emphasis on hospitality, retail, tourism, and related sectors. The placement scenario at IIHMR Jaipur is generally favorable, owing to its industry connections, dedicated placement cell, and the comprehensive curriculum that aligns with market demands. Here's an overview of the placement landscape at IIHMR Jaipur:\n\n### **1. Placement Statistics**\n- **Placement Rate:** IIHMR Jaipur typically boasts a high placement rate, often exceeding 80-90% across various programs. The exact percentage can vary each year based on the economic climate, industry demand, and other factors.\n- **Internship Opportunities:** Before final placements, students undergo internships that are integral to their training. These internships not only provide practical experience but also serve as a pipeline for potential full-time offers.\n\n### **2. Average and Highest Packages**\n- **Average Salary Package:** The average salary package for graduates can range between INR 3 to 6 lakhs per annum, depending on the program, job role, and the recruiting company.\n- **Highest Salary Package:** Top performers and those recruited by multinational corporations or renowned hospitality brands have secured packages upwards of INR 12 lakhs per annum.\n\n### **3. Top Recruiting Companies**\nIIHMR Jaipur attracts a diverse array of recruiters from various sectors related to hospitality, retail, tourism, and management. Some of the prominent recruiters include:\n- **Hospitality & Tourism:** Taj Hotels, Marriott International, Oberoi Group, AccorHotels, Hyatt Hotels, Lemon Tree Hotels, and ITC Hotels.\n- **Retail Management:** Future Group, Reliance Retail, Shoppers Stop, and Spencer\u2019s Retail.\n- **Travel & Aviation:** MakeMyTrip, Yatra, Air India, Indigo, and Uber.\n- **Food & Beverage:** Zomato, Swiggy, Domino\u2019s Pizza, and various FMCG companies.\n- **E-commerce & Technology:** Amazon, Flipkart, and other tech-driven startups focusing on the hospitality sector.\n- **Consulting & Management Firms:** Deloitte, KPMG, and niche consulting firms related to hospitality and tourism.\n  \n### **4. Placement Support and Career Services**\n- **Dedicated Placement Cell:** IIHMR Jaipur has a proactive placement cell that facilitates interactions between students and recruiters. They organize campus recruitment drives, job fairs, and pre-placement training sessions.\n- **Skill Development:** The university offers various workshops, seminars, and training programs to enhance students' soft skills, communication abilities, and technical knowledge pertinent to their desired career paths.\n- **Alumni Network:** A strong alumni network often aids in mentoring current students, providing industry insights, and sometimes facilitating job referrals.\n\n### **5. Global Opportunities**\nGiven IIHMR Jaipur's international collaborations and its focus on global standards in hospitality education, graduates often find opportunities not just in India but also abroad. Programs with international exposure or exchange components further enhance employability in global markets.\n\n### **6. Entrepreneurship Support**\nFor students inclined towards starting their ventures, IIHMR Jaipur provides resources and support through incubation centers, mentorship programs, and workshops focused on entrepreneurship in the hospitality and retail sectors.\n\n### **Conclusion**\nOverall, IIHMR Jaipur offers a robust placement ecosystem supported by its specialized programs, industry ties, and dedicated career services. Prospective students can expect ample opportunities in various sectors related to their fields of study, backed by comprehensive support to navigate their career paths successfully.\n\n**Note:** Placement statistics and opportunities can fluctuate based on economic conditions, industry trends, and individual student performance. It's advisable to consult the latest placement reports from IIHMR Jaipur or reach out directly to their placement cell for the most recent and detailed information.",
